===2010 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2010, there were 1,226 people, 534 households, and 324 families residing in the city. The [[population density]] was 1,106 people per square mile. There were 549 housing units at an average density of 499 per square mile. The racial makeup of the city was 99.1% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.2% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.2% from two or more races.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shullsburg, Wisconsin|url=http://www.city-data.com/city/Shullsburg-Wisconsin.html|work=City-Data.com|publisher=City-Data|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_10_5YR_B25001&prodType=table|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=28 August 2012}}{{dead link|bot=medic|date=April 2020}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref name="American FactFinder">{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_SF1_QTP11&prodType=table|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212054906/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_SF1_QTP11&prodType=table|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 February 2020|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref>

There were 534 households, of which 60.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 47.8% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 39.3% were non-families. 35.4% of all households were made up of individuals. The average household size was 2.3 and the average family size was 2.96.<ref name="American FactFinder"/>

In the city, the population was spread out, with 24.4% under the age of 18, 7.9% from 18 to 24, 21.5% from 25 to 44, 29.8% from 45 to 64, and 17.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.3 years. For every 100 females, there were 94.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.7 males.<ref>{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_SF2_QTP1&prodType=table|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212210714/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=DEC_10_SF2_QTP1&prodType=table|url-status=dead|archive-date=12 February 2020|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref>

